title: Bryant's Station and the Memorial Proceedings Held on Its Site Under the Auspices of the Lexington Chapter, D. A. R., August the 18th, 1896, in Honor of Its Heroic Mothers and Daughters
subtitle: George R. R. Martin's alternate-history story revolves around one of six "geeks" sent back to a critical point in history. Their mission is to prevent the Swedish fortress of Sveaborg from surrendering to the Russians in order to win the war - or "maybe [to] just save ourselves from the plagues and bombs and the poisoned winds".
authors: Daughters of the American Revolution. Kentucky State Society. Lexington Chapter
publisher: Louisville, Ky., J. P. Morton, printers
